  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The near horizon geometry of the rotating C-metric, describing accelerating Kerr–Newman black holes, is analysed. It is shown that, at extremality, even though it is not isomorphic to the extremal Kerr–Newman, it remains a warped and twisted product of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="italic">AdS</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> . Therefore the methods of the Kerr/CFT correspondence can successfully be applied to build a CFT dual model, whose entropy reproduces, through the Cardy formula, the Bekenstein–Hawking entropy of the accelerating black hole.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
